oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Blood samples from 160 dairy animals in 15 client herds were tested for titers to Bovine Virus Diarrhea (BYD), Infectious Bovine Rhinotracheitis (IBR), Parainfluenza 3 (PI3), and Bovine Respiratory Syncytial Virus (BRSV). Sampling occurred from September through December, 1984. Data from other surveys in the same geographical area are included in the 9-18 month age group summary.
